163constexpr size_t kGraphAssemblerLabelDynamicCount = ~0u;
164
165template <size_t VarCount>
166struct GraphAssemblerHelper {
167 template <typename T>
168 using Array = std::array<T, VarCount>;
169 static constexpr bool kIsDynamic = false;
170
171 static Array<Node*> InitNodeArray(const Array<MachineRepresentation>& reps) {
172 return {};
173 }
174};
175template <>
176struct GraphAssemblerHelper<kGraphAssemblerLabelDynamicCount> {
177 // TODO(leszeks): We could allow other sizes of small vector here, by encoding
178 // the size in the negative VarCount.
179 template <typename T>
180 using Array = base::SmallVector<T, 4>;
181 static constexpr bool kIsDynamic = true;
182
183 static Array<Node*> InitNodeArray(const Array<MachineRepresentation>& reps) {
184 return Array<Node*>(reps.size());
185 }
186};
187} // namespace detail

189// Label with statically known count of incoming branches and phis.
190template <size_t VarCount>
191class GraphAssemblerLabel {
192 using Helper = detail::GraphAssemblerHelper<VarCount>;
193 template <typename T>
194 using Array = typename Helper::template Array<T>;
195 static constexpr bool kIsDynamic = Helper::kIsDynamic;
196
197 public:
198 size_t Count() { return representations_.size(); }
199
200 Node* PhiAt(size_t index);
201
202 template <typename T>
203 TNode<T> PhiAt(size_t index) {
204 // TODO(jgruber): Investigate issues on ptr compression bots and enable.
205 // DCHECK(IsMachineRepresentationOf<T>(representations_[index]));
206 return TNode<T>::UncheckedCast(PhiAt(index));
207 }
208
209 bool IsUsed() const { return merged_count_ > 0; }
210
211 GraphAssemblerLabel(GraphAssemblerLabelType type, int loop_nesting_level,
212 Array<MachineRepresentation> reps)
213 : type_(type),
214 loop_nesting_level_(loop_nesting_level),
215 bindings_(Helper::InitNodeArray(reps)),
216 representations_(std::move(reps)) {}
217
218 ~GraphAssemblerLabel() { DCHECK(IsBound() || merged_count_ == 0); }
219
220 private:
221 friend class GraphAssembler;
222
223 void SetBound() {
224 DCHECK(!IsBound());
225 is_bound_ = true;
226 }
227 bool IsBound() const { return is_bound_; }
228 bool IsDeferred() const {
229 return type_ == GraphAssemblerLabelType::kDeferred;
230 }
231 bool IsLoop() const { return type_ == GraphAssemblerLabelType::kLoop; }
232
233 bool is_bound_ = false;
234 const GraphAssemblerLabelType type_;
235 const int loop_nesting_level_;
236 size_t merged_count_ = 0;
237 Node* effect_;
238 Node* control_;
239 Array<Node*> bindings_;
240 const Array<MachineRepresentation> representations_;
241};

244 GraphAssemblerLabel<detail::kGraphAssemblerLabelDynamicCount>;

247template <typename T, typename Enable, typename... Us>
248struct GraphAssemblerLabelForXHelper;
249
250// If the Us are a template pack each assignable to T, use a static label.
251template <typename T, typename... Us>
252struct GraphAssemblerLabelForXHelper<
253 T, std::enable_if_t<std::conjunction_v<std::is_assignable<T&, Us>...>>,
254 Us...> {
255 using Type = GraphAssemblerLabel<sizeof...(Us)>;
256};
257
258// If the single arg is a vector of U assignable to T, use a dynamic label.
259template <typename T, typename U>
260struct GraphAssemblerLabelForXHelper<
261 T, std::enable_if_t<std::is_assignable_v<T&, U>>, base::SmallVector<U, 4>> {
262 using Type = GraphAssemblerDynamicLabel;
263};
264
265template <typename... Vars>
266using GraphAssemblerLabelForVars =
267 typename GraphAssemblerLabelForXHelper<Node*, void, Vars...>::Type;
268
269template <typename... Reps>
270using GraphAssemblerLabelForReps =
271 typename GraphAssemblerLabelForXHelper<MachineRepresentation, void,
272 Reps...>::Type;

564 // Updates machinery for creating {LoopExit,LoopExitEffect,LoopExitValue}
565 // nodes on loop exits (which are necessary for loop peeling).
566 //
567 // All labels created while a LoopScope is live are considered to be inside
568 // the loop.
569 template <MachineRepresentation... Reps>
570 class V8_NODISCARD LoopScope final {
571 private:
572 // The internal scope is only here to increment the graph assembler's
573 // nesting level prior to `loop_header_label` creation below.
574 class V8_NODISCARD LoopScopeInternal {
575 public:
576 explicit LoopScopeInternal(GraphAssembler* gasm)
577 : previous_loop_nesting_level_(gasm->loop_nesting_level_),
578 gasm_(gasm) {
579 gasm->loop_nesting_level_++;
580 }
581
582 ~LoopScopeInternal() {
583 gasm_->loop_nesting_level_--;
584 DCHECK_EQ(gasm_->loop_nesting_level_, previous_loop_nesting_level_);
585 }
586
587 private:
588 const int previous_loop_nesting_level_;
589 GraphAssembler* const gasm_;
590 };
591
592 public:
593 explicit LoopScope(GraphAssembler* gasm)
594 : internal_scope_(gasm),
595 gasm_(gasm),
596 loop_header_label_(gasm->MakeLoopLabel(Reps...)) {
597 // This feature may only be used if it has been enabled.
598 DCHECK(gasm_->mark_loop_exits_);
599 gasm->loop_headers_.push_back(&loop_header_label_.control_);
600 DCHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(gasm_->loop_headers_.size()),
601 gasm_->loop_nesting_level_);
602 }
603
604 ~LoopScope() {
605 DCHECK_EQ(static_cast<int>(gasm_->loop_headers_.size()),
606 gasm_->loop_nesting_level_);
607 gasm_->loop_headers_.pop_back();
608 }
609
610 GraphAssemblerLabel<sizeof...(Reps)>* loop_header_label() {
611 return &loop_header_label_;
612 }
613
614 private:
615 const LoopScopeInternal internal_scope_;
616 GraphAssembler* const gasm_;
617 GraphAssemblerLabel<sizeof...(Reps)> loop_header_label_;
618 };

645
646 Zone* temp_zone_;
647 MachineGraph* mcgraph_;
648 BranchSemantics default_branch_semantics_;
649 Node* effect_;
650 Node* control_;
651 // {node_changed_callback_} should be called when a node outside the
652 // subgraph created by the graph assembler changes.
653 base::Optional<NodeChangedCallback> node_changed_callback_;
654
655 // Inline reducers enable reductions to be performed to nodes as they are
656 // added to the graph with the graph assembler.
657 ZoneVector<Reducer*> inline_reducers_;
658 bool inline_reductions_blocked_;
659
660 // Track loop information in order to properly mark loop exits with
661 // {LoopExit,LoopExitEffect,LoopExitValue} nodes. The outermost level has
662 // a nesting level of 0. See also GraphAssembler::LoopScope.
663 int loop_nesting_level_ = 0;
664 ZoneVector<Node**> loop_headers_;
665
666 // Feature configuration. As more features are added, this should be turned
667 // into a bitfield.
668 const bool mark_loop_exits_;
669};

673 DCHECK(IsBound());

678template <typename... Vars>
679void GraphAssembler::MergeState(
680 detail::GraphAssemblerLabelForVars<Vars...>* label, Vars... vars) {
681 using NodeArray = typename detail::GraphAssemblerLabelForVars<
682 Vars...>::template Array<Node*>;
683 RestoreEffectControlScope restore_effect_control_scope(this);
684
685 const int merged_count = static_cast<int>(label->merged_count_);
686
687 const size_t var_count = label->Count();
688 NodeArray var_array{vars...};
689
690 const bool is_loop_exit = label->loop_nesting_level_ != loop_nesting_level_;
691 if (is_loop_exit) {
692 // This feature may only be used if it has been enabled.
693 USE(mark_loop_exits_);
694 DCHECK(mark_loop_exits_);
695 // Jumping from loops to loops not supported.
696 DCHECK(!label->IsLoop());
697 // Currently only the simple case of jumping one level is supported.
698 DCHECK_EQ(label->loop_nesting_level_, loop_nesting_level_ - 1);
699 DCHECK(!loop_headers_.empty());
700 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(*loop_headers_.back());
701
702 // Mark this exit to enable loop peeling.
703 AddNode(graph()->NewNode(common()->LoopExit(), control(),
704 *loop_headers_.back()));
705 AddNode(graph()->NewNode(common()->LoopExitEffect(), effect(), control()));
706 for (size_t i = 0; i < var_count; i++) {
707 var_array[i] = AddNode(graph()->NewNode(
708 common()->LoopExitValue(MachineRepresentation::kTagged), var_array[i],
709 control()));
710 }
711 }
712
713 if (label->IsLoop()) {
714 if (merged_count == 0) {
715 DCHECK(!label->IsBound());
716 label->control_ =
717 graph()->NewNode(common()->Loop(2), control(), control());
718 label->effect_ = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), effect(),
719 effect(), label->control_);
720 Node* terminate = graph()->NewNode(common()->Terminate(), label->effect_,
721 label->control_);
722 NodeProperties::MergeControlToEnd(graph(), common(), terminate);
723 for (size_t i = 0; i < var_count; i++) {
724 label->bindings_[i] =
725 graph()->NewNode(common()->Phi(label->representations_[i], 2),
726 var_array[i], var_array[i], label->control_);
727 }
728 } else {
729 DCHECK(label->IsBound());
730 DCHECK_EQ(1, merged_count);
731 label->control_->ReplaceInput(1, control());
732 label->effect_->ReplaceInput(1, effect());
733 for (size_t i = 0; i < var_count; i++) {
734 label->bindings_[i]->ReplaceInput(1, var_array[i]);
735 CHECK(!NodeProperties::IsTyped(var_array[i])); // Unsupported.
736 }
737 }
738 } else {
739 DCHECK(!label->IsLoop());
740 DCHECK(!label->IsBound());
741 if (merged_count == 0) {
742 // Just set the control, effect and variables directly.
743 label->control_ = control();
744 label->effect_ = effect();
745 for (size_t i = 0; i < var_count; i++) {
746 label->bindings_[i] = var_array[i];
747 }
748 } else if (merged_count == 1) {
749 // Create merge, effect phi and a phi for each variable.
750 label->control_ =
751 graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(2), label->control_, control());
752 label->effect_ = graph()->NewNode(common()->EffectPhi(2), label->effect_,
753 effect(), label->control_);
754 for (size_t i = 0; i < var_count; i++) {
755 label->bindings_[i] = graph()->NewNode(
756 common()->Phi(label->representations_[i], 2), label->bindings_[i],
757 var_array[i], label->control_);
758 }
759 } else {
760 // Append to the merge, effect phi and phis.
761 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kMerge, label->control_->opcode());
762 label->control_->AppendInput(graph()->zone(), control());
763 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(label->control_,
764 common()->Merge(merged_count + 1));
765
766 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kEffectPhi, label->effect_->opcode());
767 label->effect_->ReplaceInput(merged_count, effect());
768 label->effect_->AppendInput(graph()->zone(), label->control_);
769 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(label->effect_,
770 common()->EffectPhi(merged_count + 1));
771
772 for (size_t i = 0; i < var_count; i++) {
773 DCHECK_EQ(IrOpcode::kPhi, label->bindings_[i]->opcode());
774 label->bindings_[i]->ReplaceInput(merged_count, var_array[i]);
775 label->bindings_[i]->AppendInput(graph()->zone(), label->control_);
776 NodeProperties::ChangeOp(
777 label->bindings_[i],
778 common()->Phi(label->representations_[i], merged_count + 1));
779 if (NodeProperties::IsTyped(label->bindings_[i])) {
780 CHECK(NodeProperties::IsTyped(var_array[i]));
781 Type old_type = NodeProperties::GetType(label->bindings_[i]);
782 Type new_type = Type::Union(
783 old_type, NodeProperties::GetType(var_array[i]), graph()->zone());
784 NodeProperties::SetType(label->bindings_[i], new_type);
785 }
786 }
787 }
788 }
789 label->merged_count_++;
790}

792template <size_t VarCount>
793void GraphAssembler::Bind(GraphAssemblerLabel<VarCount>* label) {
794 DCHECK_NULL(control());
795 DCHECK_NULL(effect());
796 DCHECK_LT(0, label->merged_count_);
797 DCHECK_EQ(label->loop_nesting_level_, loop_nesting_level_);
798
799 control_ = label->control_;
800 effect_ = label->effect_;
801
802 label->SetBound();
803
804 if (label->merged_count_ > 1 || label->IsLoop()) {
805 AddNode(label->control_);
806 AddNode(label->effect_);
807 for (size_t i = 0; i < label->Count(); i++) {
808 AddNode(label->bindings_[i]);
809 }
810 } else {
811 // If the basic block does not have a control node, insert a dummy
812 // Merge node, so that other passes have a control node to start from.
813 control_ = AddNode(graph()->NewNode(common()->Merge(1), control()));
814 }
815}

873 effect_ = nullptr;

1101 // A catch scope represents a single catch handler. The handler can be
1102 // custom catch logic within the reduction itself; or a catch handler in the
1103 // outside graph into which the reduction will be integrated (in this case
1104 // the scope is called 'outermost').
1105 class V8_NODISCARD CatchScope {
1106 private:
1107 // Only used to partially construct the outermost scope.
1108 explicit CatchScope(Zone* zone) : if_exception_nodes_(zone) {}
1109
1110 // For all inner scopes.
1111 CatchScope(Zone* zone, JSGraphAssembler* gasm)
1112 : gasm_(gasm),
1113 parent_(gasm->catch_scope_),
1114 has_handler_(true),
1115 if_exception_nodes_(zone) {
1116 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(gasm_);
1117 gasm_->catch_scope_ = this;
1118 }
1119
1120 public:
1121 ~CatchScope() { gasm_->catch_scope_ = parent_; }
1122
1123 static CatchScope Outermost(Zone* zone) { return CatchScope{zone}; }
1124 static CatchScope Inner(Zone* zone, JSGraphAssembler* gasm) {
1125 return {zone, gasm};
1126 }
1127
1128 bool has_handler() const { return has_handler_; }
1129 bool is_outermost() const { return parent_ == nullptr; }
1130 CatchScope* parent() const { return parent_; }
1131
1132 // Should only be used to initialize the outermost scope (inner scopes
1133 // always have a handler and are passed the gasm pointer at construction).
1134 void set_has_handler(bool v) {
1135 DCHECK(is_outermost());
1136 has_handler_ = v;
1137 }
1138 void set_gasm(JSGraphAssembler* v) {
1139 DCHECK(is_outermost());
1140 DCHECK_NOT_NULL(v);
1141 gasm_ = v;
1142 }
1143
1144 bool has_exceptional_control_flow() const {
1145 return !if_exception_nodes_.empty();
1146 }
1147
1148 void RegisterIfExceptionNode(Node* if_exception) {
1149 DCHECK(has_handler());
1150 if_exception_nodes_.push_back(if_exception);
1151 }
1152
1153 void MergeExceptionalPaths(TNode<Object>* exception_out, Effect* effect_out,
1154 Control* control_out) {
1155 DCHECK(has_handler());
1156 DCHECK(has_exceptional_control_flow());
1157
1158 const int size = static_cast<int>(if_exception_nodes_.size());
1159
1160 if (size == 1) {
1161 // No merge needed.
1162 Node* e = if_exception_nodes_.at(0);
1163 *exception_out = TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(e);
1164 *effect_out = Effect(e);
1165 *control_out = Control(e);
1166 } else {
1167 DCHECK_GT(size, 1);
1168
1169 Node* merge = gasm_->graph()->NewNode(gasm_->common()->Merge(size),
1170 size, if_exception_nodes_.data());
1171
1172 // These phis additionally take {merge} as an input. Temporarily add
1173 // it to the list.
1174 if_exception_nodes_.push_back(merge);
1175 const int size_with_merge =
1176 static_cast<int>(if_exception_nodes_.size());
1177
1178 Node* ephi = gasm_->graph()->NewNode(gasm_->common()->EffectPhi(size),
1179 size_with_merge,
1180 if_exception_nodes_.data());
1181 Node* phi = gasm_->graph()->NewNode(
1182 gasm_->common()->Phi(MachineRepresentation::kTagged, size),
1183 size_with_merge, if_exception_nodes_.data());
1184 if_exception_nodes_.pop_back();
1185
1186 *exception_out = TNode<Object>::UncheckedCast(phi);
1187 *effect_out = Effect(ephi);
1188 *control_out = Control(merge);
1189 }
1190 }
1191
1192 private:
1193 JSGraphAssembler* gasm_ = nullptr;
1194 CatchScope* const parent_ = nullptr;
1195 bool has_handler_ = false;
1196 NodeVector if_exception_nodes_;
1197 };

1202 using NodeGenerator0 = std::function<TNode<Object>()>;
1203 // TODO(jgruber): Currently, it's the responsibility of the developer to note
1204 // which operations may throw and appropriately wrap these in a call to
1205 // MayThrow (see e.g. JSCall3 and CallRuntime2). A more methodical approach
1206 // would be good.
1207 TNode<Object> MayThrow(const NodeGenerator0& body) {
1208 TNode<Object> result = body();
1209
1210 if (catch_scope()->has_handler()) {
1211 // The IfException node is later merged into the outer graph.
1212 // Note: AddNode is intentionally not called since effect and control
1213 // should not be updated.
1214 Node* if_exception =
1215 graph()->NewNode(common()->IfException(), effect(), control());
1216 catch_scope()->RegisterIfExceptionNode(if_exception);
1217
1218 // Control resumes here.
1219 AddNode(graph()->NewNode(common()->IfSuccess(), control()));
1220 }
1221
1222 return result;
1223 }

1225 using VoidGenerator0 = std::function<void()>;
1226 // TODO(jgruber): Currently IfBuilder0 and IfBuilder1 are implemented as
1227 // separate classes. If, in the future, we encounter additional use cases that
1228 // return more than 1 value, we should merge these back into a single variadic
1229 // implementation.
1230 class IfBuilder0 final {
1231 public:
1232 IfBuilder0(JSGraphAssembler* gasm, TNode<Boolean> cond, bool negate_cond)
1233 : gasm_(gasm),
1234 cond_(cond),
1235 negate_cond_(negate_cond),
1236 initial_effect_(gasm->effect()),
1237 initial_control_(gasm->control()) {}

1239 IfBuilder0& ExpectTrue() {
1240 DCHECK_EQ(hint_, BranchHint::kNone);

1242 return *this;
1243 }
1244 IfBuilder0& ExpectFalse() {
1245 DCHECK_EQ(hint_, BranchHint::kNone);
1246 hint_ = BranchHint::kFalse;
1247 return *this;
1248 }

1251 then_body_ = body;
1252 return *this;
1253 }

1255 else_body_ = body;
1256 return *this;
1257 }
1258
1259 ~IfBuilder0() {
1260 // Ensure correct usage: effect/control must not have been modified while
1261 // the IfBuilder0 instance is alive.
1262 DCHECK_EQ(gasm_->effect(), initial_effect_);
1263 DCHECK_EQ(gasm_->control(), initial_control_);
1264
1265 // Unlike IfBuilder1, this supports an empty then or else body. This is
1266 // possible since the merge does not take any value inputs.
1267 DCHECK(then_body_ || else_body_);
1268
1269 if (negate_cond_) std::swap(then_body_, else_body_);
1270
1271 auto if_true = (hint_ == BranchHint::kFalse) ? gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel()
1272 : gasm_->MakeLabel();
1273 auto if_false = (hint_ == BranchHint::kTrue) ? gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel()
1274 : gasm_->MakeLabel();
1275 auto merge = gasm_->MakeLabel();
1276 gasm_->Branch(cond_, &if_true, &if_false);
1277
1278 gasm_->Bind(&if_true);
1279 if (then_body_) then_body_();
1280 if (gasm_->HasActiveBlock()) gasm_->Goto(&merge);
1281
1282 gasm_->Bind(&if_false);
1283 if (else_body_) else_body_();
1284 if (gasm_->HasActiveBlock()) gasm_->Goto(&merge);
1285
1286 gasm_->Bind(&merge);
1287 }

1295 const bool negate_cond_;
1296 const Effect initial_effect_;
1297 const Control initial_control_;
1298 BranchHint hint_ = BranchHint::kNone;
1299 VoidGenerator0 then_body_;
1300 VoidGenerator0 else_body_;
1301 };

1306 template <typename T, typename Cond>
1307 class IfBuilder1 {
1308 using If1BodyFunction = std::function<TNode<T>()>;
1309
1310 public:
1311 IfBuilder1(JSGraphAssembler* gasm, TNode<Cond> cond, bool negate_cond)
1312 : gasm_(gasm), cond_(cond), negate_cond_(negate_cond) {}
1313
1314 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT IfBuilder1& ExpectTrue() {
1315 DCHECK_EQ(hint_, BranchHint::kNone);
1316 hint_ = BranchHint::kTrue;
1317 return *this;
1318 }
1319
1320 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT IfBuilder1& ExpectFalse() {
1321 DCHECK_EQ(hint_, BranchHint::kNone);
1322 hint_ = BranchHint::kFalse;
1323 return *this;
1324 }
1325
1326 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT IfBuilder1& Then(const If1BodyFunction& body) {
1327 then_body_ = body;
1328 return *this;
1329 }
1330 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT IfBuilder1& Else(const If1BodyFunction& body) {
1331 else_body_ = body;
1332 return *this;
1333 }
1334
1335 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT TNode<T> Value() {
1336 DCHECK(then_body_);
1337 DCHECK(else_body_);
1338
1339 if (negate_cond_) std::swap(then_body_, else_body_);
1340
1341 auto if_true = (hint_ == BranchHint::kFalse) ? gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel()
1342 : gasm_->MakeLabel();
1343 auto if_false = (hint_ == BranchHint::kTrue) ? gasm_->MakeDeferredLabel()
1344 : gasm_->MakeLabel();
1345 auto merge = gasm_->MakeLabel(PhiMachineRepresentationOf<T>);
1346 if constexpr (std::is_same_v<Cond, Word32T>) {
1347 gasm_->MachineBranch(cond_, &if_true, &if_false, hint_);
1348 } else {
1349 static_assert(std::is_same_v<Cond, Boolean>);
1350 if (hint_ != BranchHint::kNone) {
1351 gasm_->BranchWithHint(cond_, &if_true, &if_false, hint_);
1352 } else {
1353 gasm_->Branch(cond_, &if_true, &if_false);
1354 }
1355 }
1356
1357 gasm_->Bind(&if_true);
1358 TNode<T> then_result = then_body_();
1359 if (gasm_->HasActiveBlock()) gasm_->Goto(&merge, then_result);
1360
1361 gasm_->Bind(&if_false);
1362 TNode<T> else_result = else_body_();
1363 if (gasm_->HasActiveBlock()) {
1364 gasm_->Goto(&merge, else_result);
1365 }
1366
1367 gasm_->Bind(&merge);
1368 return merge.template PhiAt<T>(0);
1369 }
1370
1371 private:
1372 static constexpr MachineRepresentation kPhiRepresentation =
1373 MachineRepresentation::kTagged;
1374
1375 JSGraphAssembler* const gasm_;
1376 const TNode<Cond> cond_;
1377 const bool negate_cond_;
1378 BranchHint hint_ = BranchHint::kNone;
1379 If1BodyFunction then_body_;
1380 If1BodyFunction else_body_;
1381 };
